# my-project/

# A sample Go application demonstrating standard project layout with cmd/, internal/, and pkg/ directories

# This project includes a simple HTTP server and JSON parser with a public API client

go.mod
Go module definition file specifying module name and Go version requirements.

go.sum
Go module checksums for ensuring reproducible builds and dependency integrity.

Makefile
Build automation with common tasks: build, test, clean, and run commands.

cmd/
Your Application's Entry Points - Contains the main packages for your executables.

internal/
Private Application Code - The bulk of your project's logic, private to this project.

pkg/
Public Library Code - Code that is safe to be imported and used by external applications.
